However, the current economic crisis has marked a turning point.
The austerity imposed by Berlin and the European Central Bank, coupled with the strain on national economies through accession to the single currency, has led many people to think that Project Europe has gone too far.
The euro crisis has little to do with national governments experiencing excessive budget deficits – this was only true for Greece.
